Lawyers risk becoming irrelevant if they do not reach the poor and vulnerable, a professor of Law at the University of Nairobi has said.
Prof Patricia Kameri Mbote said there is need to help the poor and vulnerable to access justice.
“Just like the way we talk about the last mile connectivity, as legal fraternity we must also strive to reach the unreached in the last mile of access to justice,” said Prof Kameri on Thursday.



