Legal Aid
She was speaking at Sentrim Elementaita Lodge on the role of Law Schools in Legal Aid provision during the National Conference on Legal Aid in Kenya.
The three-day conference whose theme is: “Strengthening access to justice through legal aid” is one of the activities implemented under the Egerton University Faculty of Law Legal Aid Project.
The project is supported by European Union and United Nations Development Programme under Amkeni Wakenya Project within the programme for Legal Empowerment Aid Delivery.
